4","1420–1447":"1420–1447","1425–1478":"1425–1478","1440":"1440","1483":"1483","1493":"1493","1492":"1492","1490":"1490","1447":"1447","1425":"1425","1534":"1534","1478":"1478","1465":"1465","1442":"1442","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","ABT 1465":"about 1465","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Sassenage, Isère, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Sassenage, Isère, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France","Manningford Bruce, Wiltshire, England":"Manningford Bruce, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Sassenage, Isère, Rhône-Alpes, France":"Sassenage, Isère, Rhône-Alpes, France","Manningford Bruce, Pewsey, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Manningford Bruce, Wiltshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Berenger","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French (<b>Bérenger</b>): variant of <b>Béringer</b> (see   Beringer  ).","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Berringer  , a cognate of 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Beringer","meanings":["German; French (<b>Béringer</b>): from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Beringari</i>, <i>Beringer</i>, composed of the elements <i>bern</i> ‘bear’ + <i>ger</i> ‘spear’. Compare French   Belanger   and   Berenger  .","German: habitational name for someone from any of several paces called Behringen or Böhringen in Baden-Württemberg and Bayern. Compare   Baringer  ,   Behringer  ,   Berringer  , and   Boehringer  .","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Berringer  ."]},{"name":"Berenguer","meanings":["Spanish and French (southern; <b>Bérenguer</b>): from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>ber</i> ‘bear’ + <i>ger</i> ‘spear’, a cognate of French <b>Bérenger</b> (see   Berenger  ) and <b>Béringer</b> (see   Beringer  )."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Berenger I was born in 1442, in Sassenage, Isère, Rhône-Alpes, France, his father, Francois Berenger, was 22 and his mother, Philippa Alleman, was 18. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Katherine Luster. He died in 1483, in Manningford Bruce, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1442–1483":"1442–1483","–1490":"–1490","1442–1492":"1442–1492","1463–1493":"1463–1493","1465–1534":"1465–1534","1420–1447":"1420–1447","1425–1478":"1425–1478","1440":"1440","1483":"1483","1493":"1493","1492":"1492","1490":"1490","1447":"1447","1425":"1425","1534":"1534","1478":"1478","1465":"1465","1442":"1442","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","ABT 1465":"umbes 1465","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Sassenage, Isère, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Sassenage, Isère, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","Manningford Bruce, Wiltshire, England":"Manningford Bruce, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sassenage, Isère, Rhône-Alpes, France":"Sassenage, Isère, Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","Manningford Bruce, Pewsey, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Manningford Bruce, Wiltshire, England"},"fi":{"1442–1483":"1442–1483","–1490":"–1490","1442–1492":"1442–1492","1463–1493":"1463–1493","1465–1534":"1465–1534","1420–1447":"1420–1447","1425–1478":"1425–1478","1440":"1440","1483":"1483","1493":"1493","1492":"1492","1490":"1490","1447":"1447","1425":"1425","1534":"1534","1478":"1478","1465":"1465","